race.comment: DIVINE JUSTICE (6) has placed in both runs back from a spell, solid fresh at Kyneton then running a very good race at Sandown Lakeside in what looks a tougher race, only beaten a length into third behind two smart types. This suits perfectly and she should go close. SNAPPY PIERRO (8) is racing well. She was big odds in the same race as DIVINE JUSTICE last time but wasn't far away. She draws well and has claims. SAVANNAH CHILL (4) was just fair fresh at Ballarat but that was a fair bit stronger and she's lightly raced with plenty of upside to come. TWO SIGMA (9) hasn't been far away in two runs back and should be ready to win now despite another wide gate. SUNSHINE JENNI (5) resumes with a handy profile and has claims.
